---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Reviewer Kit | BeaconGuard Assurance"
  description="A reviewer-oriented summary of BeaconGuard as an inline runtime control boundary, policy enforcement point, fail-closed checkpoint, and evidence layer."
>
  <section class="stack-section">
    <h1>Reviewer Kit</h1>
    <p class="lead">Policy control before AI execution. Evidence after every decision.</p>
    <p>
      This page helps compliance, security, privacy, risk, audit, architecture, and technical validation reviewers understand BeaconGuard's placement, decision model, evidence surface, and non-replacement boundaries.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>BeaconGuard is</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>an inline runtime control boundary</li>
      <li>a policy enforcement point before AI execution</li>
      <li>an execution-boundary authorization layer</li>
      <li>a fail-closed checkpoint</li>
      <li>an evidence layer after allow/deny/review decisions</li>
      <li>a way to add control to existing workflows without replacing core systems</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>BeaconGuard is not</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>legal review</li>
      <li>HIPAA compliance program</li>
      <li>clinical safety review</li>
      <li>EHR</li>
      <li>AML case-management system</li>
      <li>fraud decision engine</li>
      <li>transaction monitoring platform</li>
      <li>SIEM</li>
      <li>IAM</li>
      <li>GRC</li>
      <li>model monitoring</li>
      <li>generic API gateway</li>
      <li>replacement platform</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>What reviewers can assess here</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Where BeaconGuard sits at the AI request boundary</li>
      <li>How signed request metadata, workflow identity, user role, source-system trust, approved-pathway status, context tags, freshness windows, and replay controls are evaluated</li>
      <li>How allow, deny, and needs-review decisions are returned</li>
      <li>What audit-ready evidence is produced after decisions</li>
      <li>Which existing systems remain authoritative outside BeaconGuard</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Included review materials</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/platform">Platform architecture</a></li>
      <li><a href="/healthcare">Healthcare AI control</a></li>
      <li><a href="/fintech">Financial workflow control</a></li>
      <li><a href="/proof-evidence">Proof &amp; Evidence</a></li>
      <li><a href="/deployment">Deployment boundary review</a></li>
      <li><a href="/control-responsibility-matrix">Control responsibility matrix</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Next step</h2>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/contact">Request Controlled Architecture Evaluation</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/design-partner-program">Review evaluation format</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
